We use the quartz scheduling library for this --
http://www.opensymphony.com/quartz/
The library itself is very straightforward but it took some
integration with heritrix. This is how
we use it:
- we store the schedules in a database and provide a management front-end to it
(if you only had a few schedules you can store them directly in code
or in flat files).
The schedules vary from first and third Monday of the month, to
particular days of the year.
- when a job comes time to be crawled its job execution is to build a
crawl configuration
and then heritrix hcc (http://crawler.archive.org/hcc/) picks it up
and assigns it to a crawler.

Andrea

